    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>New Top Diplomat in China</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <dateline>BEIJING, Friday, April 27</dateline>
      <abstract>
        <p>China names Yang Jiechi, former ambassador to US, as its foreign minister, replacing Li Zhaoxing (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>China named Yang Jiechi, a former ambassador to the United States, as its foreign minister on Friday, shuffling its diplomatic team as its rising economic power has given it greater sway in world affairs.</p>
        <p>Mr. Yang, 56, formerly a vice minister, is fluent in English and known for his courteous but cautious manner. He was the ambassador to the United States from 2001 to 2005.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>China named Yang Jiechi, a former ambassador to the United States, as its foreign minister on Friday, shuffling its diplomatic team as its rising economic power has given it greater sway in world affairs.</p>
        <p>Mr. Yang, 56, formerly a vice minister, is fluent in English and known for his courteous but cautious manner. He was the ambassador to the United States from 2001 to 2005.</p>
        <p>He replaces Li Zhaoxing, another English speaker and former ambassador to Washington. No reason was given for the replacement, but at 66, Mr. Li is past the retirement age for ministerial officials.</p>
      </block>
